=== '''Monthly Bitizenship Subscription''' ===
On October 1, 2019, BitLife suggested a possibility in the future that [[Bitizenship]] will be a monthly subscription rather than a one-time payment. [https://twitter.com/BitLifeApp/status/1179194875369025536] Demos with a free trial were tested in Canada and Australia. Subscriptions were only for new players and people who didn't have Bitizenship already, those who have already bought it do not have to pay additional fees. Fans criticised the greed this possibility would have and disliked that BitLife was following the idea of apps forcing monthly subscriptions when the one-time payment was seemingly fine enough.
However the decision on a monthly subscription was reversed [https://twitter.com/bitlifeapp/status/1179817779970445312] and the idea of expansion packs were going to be the likely replacement.
Since then, [[God Mode]] has been the only expansion pack besides regular Bitizenship.

=== '''[[DogLife]]''' ===
On September 29, 2021, three years after the app's first release, BitLife presented a new sister app called DogLife, a version of BitLife where players play lives being a dog rather than a human. However responses were mixed to negative, with fans asking why BitLife couldn't add another update that people were asking for. BitLifeApp clapped back at critics but controversially said that Twitter user RoyRMcFreely99 was "being a bitch"[https://twitter.com/BitLifeApp/status/1443306262343553024] when he said that nobody wanted the update. Reactions were polarising, with some who laughed at BitLifeApp for being snarky while others argued that BitLifeApp was being unprofessional to paying customers.
In addition, at the game's initial release, the dogs were overly sexual, even for the app, where they humped babies and climaxed when humping their owners. The game was released at 12+ which became controversial because the content was deemed too mature for that audience. BitLife would then change the rating to 17+ and remove graphic dialogue.

== Alternate languages ==
On November 17, 2021, BitLife collaborated with Good Game Studios from Germany to make their first internationally-localized version of BitLife, named ''BitLife: Lebenssimulator'', available in the German language to Germany, Switzerland and Austria. Soon, BitLife started a new poll asking the players what language they can work on next, out of Spanish, French, Portuguese or Icelandic. Unfortunately, languages cannot be changed to something else in the same game so far.

